{{date|September 14, 2006}}
[[Image:St George's Hall, Liverpool.JPG|thumb|right|St. George's Hall]]
The 2006 [[w:Liverpool Biennial|Liverpool Biennial]] art festival will start its ten week run on September 16, finishing on the November 26. The exhibition uses public places located across the city. 

Installation will be situated at sites across the city including [[w:St. George's Hall, Liverpool|St. George's Hall]] and [[w:Church of St Luke, Liverpool|Church of St Luke]] with specialist centers such as the [[w:Bluecoat Arts Centre|Bluecoat Arts Centre]], [[w:FACT centre|FACT centre]], [[w:Tate Liverpool|Tate Liverpool]] and the [[w:Walker Art Gallery|Walker Art Gallery]] providing exhibition space. 
[[Image:Liverpool Everyman Theatre at dusk.jpg|thumb|right|Hope Street Liverpool]]
The international '06 exhibition includes 35 commissioned works, while the 24th John Moores Exhibition of Contemporary Painting is the UK's longest running open painting competition.

The Independents is an art exhibition that runs alongside the Biennial. Several shorter festivals will run over this period including the [[w:Hope Street, Liverpool|Hope Street]] festival.

